sentences: Yukari Tamura (田村 ゆかり, Tamura Yukari, born February 27, 1976) is a Japanese voice actress and singer affiliated with Amuleto (formerly Arts Vision and I'm Enterprise).
She debuted as a voice actress in 1997, releasing her debut single "Yūki o Kudasai" on March 26, 1997.
She debuted as a voice actress in 1997, releasing her debut single "Yūki o Kudasai" on March 26, 1997.
In 2001, Tamura formed a unit called Yamato Nadeshiko alongside Yui Horie.
Two singles were released, Mō Hitori no Watashi and Merry Merrily - the latter of which was an insert song in the Love Hina Christmas Special.

On January 1, 2007, Tamura's talent management agency changed from Arts Vision to I'm Enterprise, a subsidiary of Arts Vision and on April 1, 2007, Tamura's record company officially changed from Konami to King Records, however, there was no material effect to Tamura because the actual record production of Konami is carried out by King Records.
